script = ExtResource("3_dfyaf")
category = 29
text = "Mr G was a figure who was discovered 20 years ago in Manok of Volin. Near the south border, was discovered a house with an underground laborotory that belonged to someone known as \"Mr G\". Who Mr G is remains unknown to this day, no one nearby knows of his origin, his looks or even if it is a man. The only report is of the milkman that saw him many years ago, claimed it was a tall, dark haired individual. 

He was a scientist/researcher who had a whole hidden lab under his farmhouse. The farmhouse sold grapes, that is why they called him Mr G, but reports of his signed him of as \"Eilor\". Linguists commented that Eilor means \"Enlightenment\" in an ancient western tongue. The lab in question has very bright luminescent colours, fully teched out in software and machinery even the present inventors still did not figure out. Followed by robots that moved, talked and kept the place afloat, still after what seemed to be a long time the place was in prestine condition. When he disappeared is still in question. The Manok's Science Guild, a national science corporation, camped at the farmhouse for months to scout if anyone was entering or leaving, but to no avail. It is likely that the last time he was here was 13 years prior to it being discovered, as a used newspaper from that time period was found in his living room.

Mr G's research sparked international coverage. Copies of his work were shipped to museums around the continent and the originals only to the most trustworthy ones. Things written down by Mr G revolutionised research in the many wonders hes explored, whilst leaving more questions behind. He had reports on many of these including: the time-obsessed people of the Hama Cik, the tribes of the Nolaka Island, Befre's magical Icy Hollows, the giants of the Bauland continent, history of the indigenous tribes of Zengef and their link to the First Man and many more. He was crowned as the most influential researcher of the modern era and was worshipped by the scientific community.

Yet many actually pursue the mysteries of Mr G himself and how he came about randomly with all this information. Many question how he had so many contacts, was never noticed in these places and how he had so much easy free roam around the planet, especially as Hama Cik and Befre are incredibly far apart. But yet that mystery is not yet solvable, and maybe wont be at all, but who knows as some out there even believe Mr G may still be alive."
id = 101
name = "Mr G"
gdscript = ExtResource("1_acxq6")
